codex
The patch leaves a legacy erasure gap for certain edge rows and can falsely report completion after a retry of failed telemetry redaction. These issues undermine the erasure guarantees introduced by the change.

Full review comments:

- [P1] Do not leave legacy edges unprovenanced — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:556-558
  On upgraded databases that already contain `canonical_edges` rows with `source_id IS NULL` and `logical_id IS NOT NULL`, this predicate skips the backfill even though edge `logical_id` is only a supersession identity: `purge()` resolves lifecycle targets exclusively through `canonical_nodes`, so those edge rows are not actually purge-addressable. They remain with NULL provenance and can only disappear incidentally if a connected node is purged, leaving some legacy edge content unreachable by any source erasure.

- [P2] Preserve pending telemetry redactions across retries — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:6952-6953
  If telemetry redaction fails after the delete transaction commits, the verb returns `ErasureIncomplete`, but a retry recomputes `erased_stable_ids` from the now-deleted rows and reaches this empty-id fast path, so it can return success without ever removing the leaked stable IDs from the sink. This affects the documented retry flow for `stage = "telemetry_redaction"`; the IDs need to be persisted/re-derived before treating an idempotent retry as complete.
